{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Nature's my muse and it's been my passion."},{"time":3000,"text":"As a photographer for National Geographic, I've portrayed it for many."},{"time":9000,"text":"But five years ago, I went on a personal journey."},{"time":13000,"text":"I wanted to visualize the story of life."},{"time":18000,"text":"It's the hardest thing I've ever attempted,"},{"time":20000,"text":"and there have been plenty of times when I felt like backing out."},{"time":25000,"text":"But there were also revelations."},{"time":27000,"text":"And one of those I'd like to share with you today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":32000,"text":"I went down to a remote lagoon in Australia, hoping to see the Earth"},{"time":39000,"text":"the way it was three billion years ago,"},{"time":41000,"text":"back before the sky turned blue."},{"time":46000,"text":"There's stromatolites down there --"},{"time":49000,"text":"the first living things to capture photosynthesis --"},{"time":53000,"text":"and it's the only place they still occur today."},{"time":58000,"text":"Going down there was like entering a time capsule,"},{"time":63000,"text":"and I came out with a different sense of myself in time."},{"time":69000,"text":"The oxygen exhaled by those stromatolites"},{"time":74000,"text":"is what we all breathe today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78000,"text":"Stromatolites are the heroes in my story."},{"time":82000,"text":"I hope it's a story that has some resonance for our time."},{"time":87000,"text":"It's a story about you and me, nature and science."},{"time":92000,"text":"And with that said, I'd like to invite you for"},{"time":97000,"text":"a short, brief journey of life through time."},{"time":120000,"text":"Our journey starts in space, where matter condenses into spheres over time ..."},{"time":128000,"text":"solidifying into surface, molded by fire."},{"time":141000,"text":"The fire gave way, Earth emerged -- but this was an alien planet."},{"time":152000,"text":"The moon was closer; things were different."},{"time":157000,"text":"Heat from within made geysers erupt -- that is how the oceans were born."},{"time":170000,"text":"Water froze around the poles and shaped the edges of the Earth."},{"time":184000,"text":"Water is the key to life, but in frozen form, it is a latent force."},{"time":191000,"text":"And when it vanishes, Earth becomes Mars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203000,"text":"But this planet is different -- it's roiling inside."},{"time":210000,"text":"And where that energy touches water, something new emerges: life."},{"time":216000,"text":"It arises around cracks in the Earth."},{"time":220000,"text":"Mud and minerals become substrate; there are bacteria."},{"time":228000,"text":"Learn to multiply, thickening in places ..."},{"time":238000,"text":"Growing living structures under an alien sky ..."},{"time":247000,"text":"Stromatolites were the first to exhale oxygen."},{"time":255000,"text":"And they changed the atmosphere."},{"time":258000,"text":"A breath that's fossilized now as iron."}]},{"cues":[{"time":266000,"text":"Meteorites delivered chemistry, and perhaps membranes, too."},{"time":272000,"text":"Life needs a membrane to contain itself"},{"time":277000,"text":"so it can replicate and mutate."},{"time":284000,"text":"These are diatoms, single-celled phytoplankton"},{"time":293000,"text":"with skeletons of silicon ..."},{"time":296000,"text":"circuit boards of the future."},{"time":302000,"text":"Shallow seas nurtured life early on, and that's where it morphed"},{"time":310000,"text":"into more complex forms."},{"time":315000,"text":"It grew as light and oxygen increased."},{"time":323000,"text":"Life hardened and became defensive."},{"time":330000,"text":"It learned to move and began to see. The first eyes grew on trilobites."},{"time":345000,"text":"Vision was refined in horseshoe crabs,"},{"time":349000,"text":"among the first to leave the sea."},{"time":354000,"text":"They still do what they've done for ages, their enemies long gone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361000,"text":"Scorpions follow prey out of the sea. Slugs became snails."},{"time":368000,"text":"Fish tried amphibian life. Frogs adapted to deserts."},{"time":378000,"text":"Lichens arose as a co-op. Fungi married algae ..."},{"time":383000,"text":"clinging to rock, and eating it too ... transforming barren land."},{"time":395000,"text":"True land plants arose, leafless at first."},{"time":401000,"text":"Once they learn how to stay upright, they grew in size and shape."},{"time":407000,"text":"The fundamental forms of ferns followed,"},{"time":415000,"text":"to bear spores that foreshadowed seeds."},{"time":419000,"text":"Life flourished in swamps."}]},{"cues":[{"time":423000,"text":"On land, life turned a corner. Jaws formed first; teeth came later."},{"time":431000,"text":"Leatherbacks and tuataras are echoes from that era."},{"time":440000,"text":"It took time for life to break away from water,"},{"time":444000,"text":"and it still beckons all the time."},{"time":448000,"text":"Life turned hard so it could venture inland."},{"time":456000,"text":"And the dragons that arose are still among us today."},{"time":475000,"text":"Jurassic Park still shimmers in part of Madagascar,"},{"time":480000,"text":"and the center of Brazil,"},{"time":484000,"text":"where plants called \"cycads\" remain rock hard."},{"time":495000,"text":"Forests arose and nurtured things with wings."},{"time":504000,"text":"One early form left an imprint, like it died only yesterday."},{"time":510000,"text":"And others fly today like echoes of the past."},{"time":516000,"text":"In birds, life gained new mobility."},{"time":528000,"text":"Flamingos covered continents. Migrations got underway."}]},{"cues":[{"time":539000,"text":"Birds witnessed the emergence of flowering plants."},{"time":544000,"text":"Water lilies were among the first."},{"time":553000,"text":"Plants began to diversify and grew, turning into trees."},{"time":564000,"text":"In Australia, a lily turned into a grass tree,"},{"time":573000,"text":"and in Hawaii, a daisy became a silver sword."},{"time":582000,"text":"In Africa, Gondwana molded Proteas."},{"time":588000,"text":"But when that ancient continent broke up, life got lusher."},{"time":594000,"text":"Tropical rainforests arose, sparking new layers of interdependence."},{"time":603000,"text":"Fungi multiplied. Orchids emerged, genitalia shaped to lure insects ..."},{"time":618000,"text":"a trick shared by the largest flower on Earth."},{"time":625000,"text":"Co-evolution entwined insects and birds and plants forever."},{"time":636000,"text":"When birds can't fly, they become vulnerable."},{"time":640000,"text":"Kiwis are, and so are these hawks trapped near Antarctica."}]},{"cues":[{"time":649000,"text":"Extinction can come slowly, but sometimes it arrives fast."},{"time":657000,"text":"An asteroid hits, and the world went down in flames."},{"time":663000,"text":"But there were witnesses, survivors in the dark."},{"time":672000,"text":"When the skies cleared, a new world was born."},{"time":679000,"text":"A world fit for mammals. From tiny shrews [came]"},{"time":686000,"text":"tenrecs, accustomed to the dark."},{"time":690000,"text":"New forms became bats. Civets."},{"time":700000,"text":"New predators, hyenas, getting faster and faster still."}]},{"cues":[{"time":712000,"text":"Grasslands created opportunities."},{"time":718000,"text":"Herd safety came with sharpened senses."},{"time":723000,"text":"Growing big was another answer, but size always comes at a price."},{"time":736000,"text":"Some mammals turned back to water."},{"time":740000,"text":"Walruses adapted with layers of fat. Sea lions got sleek."},{"time":750000,"text":"And cetaceans moved into a world without bounds."},{"time":758000,"text":"There are many ways to be a mammal. A 'roo hops in Oz;"},{"time":766000,"text":"a horse runs in Asia; and a wolf evolves stilt legs in Brazil."},{"time":782000,"text":"Primates emerge from jungles, as tarsiers first,"},{"time":791000,"text":"becoming lemurs not much later."},{"time":796000,"text":"Learning became reinforced. Bands of apes ventured into the open."},{"time":804000,"text":"And forests dried out once more. Going upright became a lifestyle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":814000,"text":"So who are we? Brothers of masculine chimps,"},{"time":820000,"text":"sisters of feminine bonobos? We are all of them, and more."},{"time":829000,"text":"We're molded by the same life force."},{"time":836000,"text":"The blood veins in our hands"},{"time":841000,"text":"echoed a course of water traces on the Earth."},{"time":846000,"text":"And our brains -- our celebrated brains --"},{"time":850000,"text":"reflect a drainage of a tidal marsh."}]},{"cues":[{"time":854000,"text":"Life is a force in its own right. It is a new element."},{"time":862000,"text":"And it has altered the Earth. It covers Earth like a skin."},{"time":874000,"text":"And where it doesn't, as in Greenland in winter,"},{"time":879000,"text":"Mars is still not very far."},{"time":884000,"text":"But that likelihood fades as long as ice melts again."},{"time":889000,"text":"And where water is liquid, it becomes a womb"},{"time":893000,"text":"for cells green with chlorophyll -- and that molecular marvel"},{"time":899000,"text":"is what's made a difference -- it powers everything."},{"time":906000,"text":"The whole animal world today lives on a stockpile"},{"time":910000,"text":"of bacterial oxygen that is cycled constantly"},{"time":913000,"text":"through plants and algae, and their waste is our breath,"},{"time":918000,"text":"and vice versa."},{"time":922000,"text":"This Earth is alive, and it's made its own membrane."},{"time":927000,"text":"We call it \"atmosphere.\" This is the icon of our journey."},{"time":937000,"text":"And you all here today can imagine and will shape where we go next."},{"time":945000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":951000,"text":"Thank you. Thank you."}]}]}